OL,3,CWhat are superinjunctions and why was
OL,4,Creporting on the Afghan relocation
OL,5,Cbanned?
OL,7,FThey can be used in a variety of
OL,8,Fcontexts, including in family and
OL,9,Fcivil courts, and can be used to
OL,10,Fprevent publishing information or
OL,11,Fnaming people.
OL,13,FInjunctions can be temporary, known as
OL,14,Finterim injunctions, or longer term `
OL,15,Feither until a future date or until a
OL,16,Ffurther order is made.
OL,18,FBreaching an injunction can be
OL,19,Fconsidered a contempt of court, which
OL,20,Fcan be punished by up to two years in
OL,21,Fprison or an unlimited fine.
